From: edi@edefix.han.de (E. v. Pappenheim)
Subject: Re: XS3-4.4 for Diamond Stealth 24?
Date: Sun, 22 Aug 1993 11:45:12 GMT

E. v. Pappenheim (edi@edefix.han.de) wrote:
: Hi,

: I'm thinkink of speeding my X a little and bying a Diamond Stealth 24 S3
: Card. Does it run with the S3-Server, and, if yes, does somebody have a working
: Xconfig? I'm running X on an ET4000 with 1152x900, does the S3-Sever (and/or 
: the Stealth) also support this resolution?

Thanks a lot to everybody who sent me help. I received about 20 mails about
this topic. A summary:

- do not use the Stealth 24, it is 'a little different' around its clockchip
  and not supported by XS3
- 1024x768 is the highest resolution with 1 Mb VRAM because XS3 installes a
  256kb cache in the videoram
- a recommended card is the Orchid Fahrenheit 1280
- XFree-2.0 will support the S3 and the Cirrus chipsets

I tried a noname card called W911 and it did not work, because the clockchip
is not supported by XS3. So I'll wait for XFree-2.0 and get a compatible card
when it is out.

Cheers,
Ecki


